Great selection of sake and whisky but I would highly suggest not to eat here. I kinda can't believe a Japanese owned place can serve hard boiled eggs in the ramen. Everything in the ramen is super average. The atmosphere is cool though. Go for drinks and karaoke.
One of my favorite spots to grab some food. great location, neat, and excellent service. I recommend this place!
Good selection of sake and Japanese vodkas and whiskeys. Off peak hours the environment is very relaxed, I'll have to come back later and see how things shake up at night.

Lovely rooftop bar that overlooks the beach. By South Beach law, furniture, decor, and staff uniforms are white in color for a very fresh and clean look.  The long but skinny infinity pool makes for great people watching and there are a lot of attractive people throughout the rooftop. The background music is pleasant but not overwhelming to prevent you from getting your game on.  The Bar is well stocked with the premium stuff.  We were here on the 4th of July last year and got a pretty good view of the city fireworks.
Went for karaoke. Found out it doesn't start till midnight

Murasaki is awesome. By far my favorite place in Streeterville. It’s in an odd location, kind of tucked away in the building but once you’re inside it has a great vibe to it. They have an extensive menu of Japanese whiskey, mixed drinks, and even some food. They play anime on a TV and on Fridays (or Saturday nights-I can’t remember) they play Japanese throwback music. You have to check Murasaki out if you’re in the area. Try one of the green tea cocktails, the less sweet one with tea is amazing
Great vibes, friendly staff.

A classic and simple izakaya in downtown. One of best sake selections in the city. They serve a great selection of izakaya style foods. Great for people looking to feel like they're back in Japan for an evening.
Cool ambiance. Terrible service

The place is cool. The drinks are great. However, the drinks took about 20 minutes. A table had their drinks taken after us and got the drink before us... The takoyaki was complete mush and was told that this is how takoyaki is. They were drenched in the sauce and fell apart as soon as you tried to pick it up. (You would have to stab the ball, which is not appropriate, to be able to put the whole thing in your mouth without falling apart.) No one at my table liked them. We've had them before so I'm not unfamiliar how they taste/what the consistency is. My table also had 5 people and we tried to move to a table that just cleared up that had more room. One of the staff said we couldn't because two people were coming to sit there. Our table was a lot smaller so we had to have someone sit on the floor because we didn't have enough seats. I understand the place is busy and small but that party could have comfortably sat at the table we were at. We left disappointed, I hope no one has an experience like ours.
Great sake, awesome server who also taught the whole group about the same tradition! DJs were fantastic who created an amazing vibe.

This place is extremely relaxing and comfortable for a couple sake drinks with some friends. It's not what I was expecting. They have at least 20+ sake varieties to choose from and I see myself slowly working through them. Super friendly and accommodating staff. I arrived 10 minutes until closingand they happily let us grab one drink.
Huge selection of Japanese liquor and amazing atmosphere and wait staff. Very pricey though!
The Karaoke machine kept breaking, but we still had a great time.
Great atmosphere and choice.
Ok, this place was really surprising. It was super small and kind of a hole in the wall but so happy I came in. Great sake and small appetizers.
A sake lovers haven. Get a big bowl full of edame to go with whatever sake you decide upon. Can't be disappointed with this place.
Great service and delicious food. Large selection of Sake if you are into that.
Very friendly service, great lunch, reasonable price

I really wanted to give this place a chance, because I thought it might be fun to have a friendly hangout where I could brush up on my Japanese, but after a few visits I found the place to be more like a tawdry hostess club. If you like Japanese draft beer, or sashimi, you will be disappointed, because they serve neither. Also, their food menu consists of instant snacks from a Japanese supermarket. I don't recommend the place, but if you find yourself there, expect to spend about $100-300 for a mediocre experience and be sure to familiarize yourself with their service-fees system before placing your first order.
wonderful experience. very Japan！

I always love coming to Murasaki Lounge. If you're looking for authentic Japanese karaoke in a private room, it's well worth it. I know they have other languages, but I never look at them. They have a one drink per hour policy when doing karaoke, which is reasonable. Food is fairly good as well, though I've only ever gotten snacks.

Not bad BUT-- here are some complaints  Out of the two mics that we were offered, only one was working properly. If you find the one that works run with it!!  The drinks (other than sochu) are E X P E N S I V E. 7 drinks were $98 for us.  Other than that, that's really it. The food was great and service was a bit slow for a monday night but very nice people. :)
Friendly service, cheap drinks, open late.

ABOUT 5 OF US ORDERED 1 ORDER OF SUSHI EACH AND WE ORDERED 2 HOURS AGO AND ARE STILL WAITING DONT COME HERE FOR FOOD. Terrible service.
Refused our business - would never recommend going to this establishment.

Shochu in Chicago is a tough find. A handful of Japanese restaurants carry a handful of varieties, but it's not something that many places carry. A notable exception is the eclectic Murasaki Lounge, which had a dozen shochus and a knowledgeable proprietress. The space is unusual in that it's got a karaoke room, a DJ booth, and low lounge-like seating where you can order from a full menu. But sit at the front bar in the low traditional Japanese chairs and enjoy a pleasant conversation with the Japanese bartenders. You're as likely to find yourself sitting next to an American who studied abroad in Tokyo as next to a Japanese executive seeking out a bit of home in the Windy City.  Kampai!
Karaoke and sake. What more do you need? Service is good. Karaoke machines seems like they have been updated in 20 years =D
Great decor, sake and vibe, but unfortunately the air conditioning was inoperable. On a 85-90 degree night, they should have been closed.
My favorite bar in Chicago - will always go there!
Really nice and cozy bar. Very nice selection of Japanese beers and shochu.
Great sake selection and cool vibe.

This place is amazing.  Pretty much as close as you can get to an authentic sake lounge in Chicago.  The sake choices are excellent and the food is pretty good.  The staff here is great.  They have karaoke booths in the back if you are so inclined.  This is a great place to chill and be able to talk with your friends.  It can get a little pricey (good sake isn't cheap), but well worth a visit.
Good
Setting straight from the 80's. Love the selection of sake.
Great Japanese whiskey here!
A really nice place where you can taste very authentic sake, although it's a bit pricy
Almost like I was transported back into one of my favorite bars in Japan. In addition to the great drink selection, there are some favorites like okonomiyaki and takoyaki (yum!).

The staff here is really courteous.  The decor is inviting and the food is delectable.  I love Suntory whiskey and had to try the moderately priced glass.  I wish I could afford to experience the $200 glass of Suntory.  They have a really good selection of sake and whiskey here.
Their private Karaoke room is the perfect place for those that like to sing but are shy to do so in public. They also have a great Sake selection.
My favorite.  Okonomiyaki & Takoyaki are the best!  Oh and Yaki Zushi and is delicious!
Great atmosphere

Tons of sake options. Had the four different small portions to get a idea of the various flavors, was sick the next day with the worst hangover. The aldehydes in sake can do a number on some, I happen to be one of them, if you are OK with it, you will love this place. The food, was fine, but not great.
Very accommodating for large groups. Wait staff seemed a little disorganized, but we were a party of 20+ so it's kind of understandable.

(Translated by Google) Authentic Japanese-owned sake lounge. Friendly staff and good selection of drinks.  (Original) Authentic Japanese-owned  sake lounge. Friendly staff and good selection of drinks. びっくりのはタコワサビがあったん!

I went here for the 1st time with my wife on Saturday night (06/27). Delicious food, great service with friendly and very nice staff. The drinks are very very good. We had great fun in the karaoke room, my wife almost died from laughing  when I sang, lol. In the end, I left a $45 tips (about 26.3%) with the guy staff/bartender in the front as our female hostess was busy with her duty. We will be back to try out more of their drinks as their list is long + the ability to customize your own drinks make it almost endless.
Fantastic atmosphere and real japanese food!
Chill,  mellow vibe with an immense selection of sake,  sochu,  and Japanese whiskeys.   Definitely a one of a kind place in Chicago.

Best place for sake and shochu in town with friends! In case the informative menu isn't enough on the drinks, the bartenders are definitely always into telling you more about what you're drinking and great for random chats too (English wasn't perfect, but it was never awkward or anything). Very attentive and cheerful staff that prevents there ever being a dull moment here. The variety on Japanese drinks is great! They also offer wonderfully done apps to go with your drinks, ranging from takoyaki to shumai to kobayashi and more. Don't intend to fill up on them, as the portions are made to compliment drinks, not to fill you up. You'll get live music here from time to time and the music volume here is just right for a casual lounge experience.The decor here is really nice and the staff keep the place really clean. I have yet to try the karaoke here, but if the service at the bar is consistent with how they handle the karaoke, I'll definitely look forward to it! Only thing keeping it from the fifth star is the high markups on some of the bottles that can be found elsewhere. Looking forward to coming back here soon!
